{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":2000,"text":"Imagine spending seven years at MIT and research laboratories,"},{"time":5000,"text":"only to find out that you're a performance artist."}]},{"cues":[{"time":10000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":14000,"text":"I'm also a software engineer,"},{"time":17000,"text":"and I make lots of different kinds of art with the computer."},{"time":19000,"text":"And I think the main thing that I'm interested in"},{"time":21000,"text":"is trying to find a way of"},{"time":23000,"text":"making the computer into a personal mode of expression."},{"time":26000,"text":"And many of you out there are the heads of Macromedia and Microsoft,"},{"time":31000,"text":"and in a way those are my bane:"},{"time":33000,"text":"I think there's a great homogenizing force"},{"time":36000,"text":"that software imposes on people and limits the way they think"},{"time":42000,"text":"about what's possible on the computer."},{"time":44000,"text":"Of course, it's also a great liberating force that makes possible,"},{"time":47000,"text":"you know, publishing and so forth, and standards, and so on."},{"time":50000,"text":"But, in a way, the computer makes possible much more"},{"time":54000,"text":"than what most people think, and my art has just been about"},{"time":57000,"text":"trying to find a personal way of using the computer,"},{"time":59000,"text":"and so I end up writing software to do that."}]},{"cues":[{"time":63000,"text":"Chris has asked me to do a short performance,"},{"time":65000,"text":"and so I'm going to take just this time -- maybe 10 minutes --"},{"time":68000,"text":"to do that, and hopefully at the end have just a moment"},{"time":70000,"text":"to show you a couple of my other projects in video form."}]},{"cues":[{"time":766000,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":768000,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":779000,"text":"We've got about a minute left."},{"time":781000,"text":"I'd just like to show a clip from a most recent project."},{"time":783000,"text":"I did a performance with two singers"},{"time":786000,"text":"who specialize in making strange noises with their mouths."},{"time":789000,"text":"And this just came off last September at ARS Electronica;"},{"time":792000,"text":"we repeated it in England."},{"time":794000,"text":"And the idea is to visualize their speech and song behind them"},{"time":797000,"text":"with a large screen."},{"time":798000,"text":"We used a computer vision tracking system"},{"time":800000,"text":"in order to know where they were."},{"time":802000,"text":"And since we know where their heads are,"},{"time":803000,"text":"and we have a wireless mic on them"},{"time":805000,"text":"that we're processing the sound from,"},{"time":806000,"text":"we're able to create visualizations"},{"time":808000,"text":"which are linked very tightly to what they're doing with their speech."},{"time":811000,"text":"This will take about 30 seconds or so."},{"time":816000,"text":"He's making a, kind of, cheek-flapping sound."}]},{"cues":[{"time":858000,"text":"Well, suffice it to say it's not all like that, but that's part of it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":861000,"text":"Thanks very much. There's always lots more."},{"time":863000,"text":"I'm overtime, so I just wanted to say you can, if you're in New York,"},{"time":865000,"text":"you can check out my work at the Whitney Biennial next week,"},{"time":867000,"text":"and also at Bitforms Gallery in Chelsea."},{"time":870000,"text":"And with that, I think I should give up the stage,"},{"time":872000,"text":"so, thank you so much."}]}]}